introduction.name: introduction
introduction.tableDefinition: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS _content_introduction (id TEXT PRIMARY KEY, "title" VARCHAR, "body" TEXT, "description" VARCHAR, "extension" VARCHAR, "meta" TEXT, "navigation" TEXT DEFAULT true, "path" VARCHAR, "seo" TEXT DEFAULT '{}', "stem" VARCHAR, "__hash__" TEXT UNIQUE);

payments.name: payments
payments.tableDefinition: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS _content_payments (id TEXT PRIMARY KEY, "title" VARCHAR, "body" TEXT, "description" VARCHAR, "extension" VARCHAR, "meta" TEXT, "navigation" TEXT DEFAULT true, "path" VARCHAR, "seo" TEXT DEFAULT '{}', "stem" VARCHAR, "__hash__" TEXT UNIQUE);

content.name: content
content.tableDefinition: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS _content_content (id TEXT PRIMARY KEY, "title" VARCHAR, "body" TEXT, "description" VARCHAR, "extension" VARCHAR, "meta" TEXT, "navigation" TEXT DEFAULT true, "path" VARCHAR, "seo" TEXT DEFAULT '{}', "stem" VARCHAR, "__hash__" TEXT UNIQUE);

info.name: info
info.tableDefinition: CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS _content_info (id TEXT PRIMARY KEY, "ready" BOOLEAN, "structureVersion" VARCHAR, "version" VARCHAR, "__hash__" TEXT UNIQUE);

icon.title: Nuxt Icon
icon.description: Configure Nuxt Icon module preferences.

attrs.title: Default Attributes
attrs.description:
Attributes applied to every icon component.

@default { "aria-hidden": true }

mode.title: Default Rendering Mode
mode.description: Set the default rendering mode for the icon component

aliases.title: Icon aliases
aliases.description: Define Icon aliases to update them easily without code changes.

cssSelectorPrefix.title: CSS Selector Prefix
cssSelectorPrefix.description: Set the default CSS selector prefix.

cssWherePseudo.title: Use CSS `:where()` Pseudo Selector
cssWherePseudo.description: Use CSS `:where()` pseudo selector to reduce specificity.

collections.title: Icon Collections
collections.description:
List of known icon collections name. Used to resolve collection name ambiguity.
e.g. `simple-icons-github` -> `simple-icons:github` instead of `simple:icons-github`

When not provided, will use the full Iconify collection list.

provider.title: Icon Provider
provider.description:
Provider to use for fetching icons

- `server` - Fetch icons with a server handler
- `iconify` - Fetch icons with Iconify API, purely client-side
- `none` - Do not fetch icons (use client bundle only)

`server` by default; `iconify` when `ssr: false`

iconifyApiEndpoint.title: Iconify API Endpoint URL
iconifyApiEndpoint.description: Define a custom Iconify API endpoint URL. Useful if you want to use a self-hosted Iconify API. Learn more: https://iconify.design/docs/api.

fallbackToApi.title: Fallback to Iconify API
fallbackToApi.description: Fallback to Iconify API if server provider fails to found the collection.

localApiEndpoint.title: Local API Endpoint Path
localApiEndpoint.description: Define a custom path for the local API endpoint.

fetchTimeout.title: Fetch Timeout
fetchTimeout.description: Set the timeout for fetching icons.

customize.title: Customize callback
customize.description: Customize icon content (replace stroke-width, colors, etc...).

tooltip.name: tooltip
tooltip.description:
Display a tooltip on the item when the menu is collapsed with the label of the item.
This has priority over the global `tooltip` prop.

text.name: text
text.description: The text content of the tooltip.

kbds.name: kbds
kbds.description: The keyboard keys to display in the tooltip.

as.name: as
as.description: The element or component this component should render as.

side.name: side
side.description:
The preferred side of the trigger to render against when open.
Will be reversed when collisions occur and avoidCollisions
is enabled.

sideOffset.name: sideOffset
sideOffset.description: The distance in pixels from the trigger.

align.name: align
align.description:
The preferred alignment against the trigger.
May change when collisions occur.

alignOffset.name: alignOffset
alignOffset.description: An offset in pixels from the `start` or `end` alignment options.

avoidCollisions.name: avoidCollisions
avoidCollisions.description:
When `true`, overrides the side and align preferences
to prevent collisions with boundary edges.

collisionBoundary.name: collisionBoundary
collisionBoundary.description:
The element used as the collision boundary. By default
this is the viewport, though you can provide additional
element(s) to be included in this check.

collisionPadding.name: collisionPadding
collisionPadding.description:
The distance in pixels from the boundary edges where collision
detection should occur. Accepts a number (same for all sides),
or a partial padding object, for example: { top: 20, left: 20 }.

arrowPadding.name: arrowPadding
arrowPadding.description:
The padding between the arrow and the edges of the content.
If your content has border-radius, this will prevent it from
overflowing the corners.

sticky.name: sticky
sticky.description:
The sticky behavior on the align axis. `partial` will keep the
content in the boundary as long as the trigger is at least partially
in the boundary whilst "always" will keep the content in the boundary
regardless.

hideWhenDetached.name: hideWhenDetached
hideWhenDetached.description: Whether to hide the content when the trigger becomes fully occluded.

positionStrategy.name: positionStrategy
positionStrategy.description: The type of CSS position property to use.

updatePositionStrategy.name: updatePositionStrategy
updatePositionStrategy.description: Strategy to update the position of the floating element on every animation frame.

forceMount.name: forceMount
forceMount.description:
Used to force mounting when more control is needed. Useful when
controlling animation with Vue animation libraries.

ariaLabel.name: ariaLabel
ariaLabel.description:
By default, screenreaders will announce the content inside
the component. If this is not descriptive enough, or you have
content that cannot be announced, use aria-label as a more
descriptive label.

disableHoverableContent.description:

disableClosingTrigger.name: disableClosingTrigger
disableClosingTrigger.description: When `true`, clicking on trigger will not close the content.

ignoreNonKeyboardFocus.name: ignoreNonKeyboardFocus
ignoreNonKeyboardFocus.description:
Prevent the tooltip from opening if the focus did not come from
the keyboard by matching against the `:focus-visible` selector.
This is useful if you want to avoid opening it when switching
browser tabs or closing a dialog.

description.name: description

props.description: When `true`, don't move the drawer upwards if there's space, but rather only change it's height so it's fully scrollable when the keyboard is open

props.name: defaultOpen
props.description: Opened by default, skips initial enter animation. Still reacts to `open` state changes

props.name: direction
props.description: Direction of the drawer. Can be `top` or `bottom`, `left`, `right`.

props.name: modal
props.description: When `false` it allows to interact with elements outside of the drawer without closing it.

props.name: closeThreshold
props.description:
Number between 0 and 1 that determines when the drawer should be closed.
Example: threshold of 0.5 would close the drawer if the user swiped for 50% of the height of the drawer or more.

props.name: setBackgroundColorOnScale
props.description: When `false` we don't change body's background color when the drawer is open.

props.name: scrollLockTimeout
props.description: Duration for which the drawer is not draggable after scrolling content inside of the drawer.

props.name: dismissible
props.description:
When `false` dragging, clicking outside, pressing esc, etc. will not close the drawer.
Use this in combination with the `open` prop, otherwise you won't be able to open/close the drawer.

props.name: noBodyStyles
props.description: When `true` the `body` doesn't get any styles assigned from Vaul

props.name: handleOnly
props.description: When `true` only allows the drawer to be dragged by the `<Drawer.Handle />` component.

props.name: snapPoints
props.description:
Array of numbers from 0 to 100 that corresponds to % of the screen a given snap point should take up.
Should go from least visible. Example `[0.2, 0.5, 0.8]`.
You can also use px values, which doesn't take screen height into account.

When `true`, overrides the side and align preferences
to prevent collisions with boundary edges.

collisionBoundary.name: collisionBoundary
collisionBoundary.description:
The element used as the collision boundary. By default
this is the viewport, though you can provide additional
element(s) to be included in this check.

collisionPadding.name: collisionPadding
collisionPadding.description:
The distance in pixels from the boundary edges where collision
detection should occur. Accepts a number (same for all sides),
or a partial padding object, for example: { top: 20, left: 20 }.

arrowPadding.name: arrowPadding
arrowPadding.description:
The padding between the arrow and the edges of the content.
If your content has border-radius, this will prevent it from
overflowing the corners.

sticky.name: sticky
sticky.description:
The sticky behavior on the align axis. `partial` will keep the
content in the boundary as long as the trigger is at least partially
in the boundary whilst "always" will keep the content in the boundary
regardless.

hideWhenDetached.name: hideWhenDetached
hideWhenDetached.description: Whether to hide the content when the trigger becomes fully occluded.

positionStrategy.name: positionStrategy
positionStrategy.description: The type of CSS position property to use.

updatePositionStrategy.name: updatePositionStrategy
updatePositionStrategy.description: Strategy to update the position of the floating element on every animation frame.

disableUpdateOnLayoutShift.name: disableUpdateOnLayoutShift
disableUpdateOnLayoutShift.description: Whether to disable the update position for the content when the layout shifted.

prioritizePosition.name: prioritizePosition
prioritizePosition.description:
Force content to be position within the viewport.

Might overlap the reference element, which may not be desired.

reference.name: reference
reference.description:
The custom element or virtual element that will be set as the reference
to position the floating element.

If provided, it will replace the default anchor element.

When `true`, hover/focus/click interactions will be disabled on elements outside
the `DismissableLayer`. Users will need to click twice on outside elements to
interact with them: once to close the `DismissableLayer`, and again to trigger the element.

When `true`, overrides the side and align preferences
to prevent collisions with boundary edges.

collisionBoundary.name: collisionBoundary
collisionBoundary.description:
The element used as the collision boundary. By default
this is the viewport, though you can provide additional
element(s) to be included in this check.

collisionPadding.name: collisionPadding
collisionPadding.description:
The distance in pixels from the boundary edges where collision
detection should occur. Accepts a number (same for all sides),
or a partial padding object, for example: { top: 20, left: 20 }.

arrowPadding.name: arrowPadding
arrowPadding.description:
The padding between the arrow and the edges of the content.
If your content has border-radius, this will prevent it from
overflowing the corners.

sticky.name: sticky
sticky.description:
The sticky behavior on the align axis. `partial` will keep the
content in the boundary as long as the trigger is at least partially
in the boundary whilst "always" will keep the content in the boundary
regardless.

hideWhenDetached.name: hideWhenDetached
hideWhenDetached.description: Whether to hide the content when the trigger becomes fully occluded.

positionStrategy.name: positionStrategy
positionStrategy.description: The type of CSS position property to use.

updatePositionStrategy.name: updatePositionStrategy
updatePositionStrategy.description: Strategy to update the position of the floating element on every animation frame.

disableUpdateOnLayoutShift.name: disableUpdateOnLayoutShift
disableUpdateOnLayoutShift.description: Whether to disable the update position for the content when the layout shifted.

prioritizePosition.name: prioritizePosition
prioritizePosition.description:
Force content to be position within the viewport.

Might overlap the reference element, which may not be desired.

reference.name: reference
reference.description:
The custom element or virtual element that will be set as the reference
to position the floating element.

If provided, it will replace the default anchor element.

Will be reversed when collisions occur and avoidCollisions
is enabled.

sideOffset.description: The distance in pixels from the trigger.

alignOffset.description: An offset in pixels from the `start` or `end` alignment options.

avoidCollisions.name: avoidCollisions
avoidCollisions.description:
When `true`, overrides the side and align preferences
to prevent collisions with boundary edges.

collisionBoundary.name: collisionBoundary
collisionBoundary.description:
The element used as the collision boundary. By default
this is the viewport, though you can provide additional
element(s) to be included in this check.

collisionPadding.name: collisionPadding
collisionPadding.description:
The distance in pixels from the boundary edges where collision
detection should occur. Accepts a number (same for all sides),
or a partial padding object, for example: { top: 20, left: 20 }.

arrowPadding.name: arrowPadding
arrowPadding.description:
The padding between the arrow and the edges of the content.
If your content has border-radius, this will prevent it from
overflowing the corners.

sticky.name: sticky
sticky.description:
The sticky behavior on the align axis. `partial` will keep the
content in the boundary as long as the trigger is at least partially
in the boundary whilst "always" will keep the content in the boundary
regardless.

hideWhenDetached.name: hideWhenDetached
hideWhenDetached.description: Whether to hide the content when the trigger becomes fully occluded.

positionStrategy.name: positionStrategy
positionStrategy.description: The type of CSS position property to use.

updatePositionStrategy.name: updatePositionStrategy
updatePositionStrategy.description: Strategy to update the position of the floating element on every animation frame.

disableUpdateOnLayoutShift.name: disableUpdateOnLayoutShift
disableUpdateOnLayoutShift.description: Whether to disable the update position for the content when the layout shifted.

prioritizePosition.name: prioritizePosition
prioritizePosition.description:
Force content to be position within the viewport.

Might overlap the reference element, which may not be desired.

reference.name: reference
reference.description:
The custom element or virtual element that will be set as the reference
to position the floating element.

If provided, it will replace the default anchor element.

side.description:
The preferred side of the trigger to render against when open.
Will be reversed when collisions occur and avoidCollisions
is enabled.

sideOffset.name: sideOffset
sideOffset.description: The distance in pixels from the trigger.

align.name: align
align.description:
The preferred alignment against the trigger.
May change when collisions occur.

alignOffset.name: alignOffset
alignOffset.description: An offset in pixels from the `start` or `end` alignment options.

avoidCollisions.name: avoidCollisions
avoidCollisions.description:
When `true`, overrides the side and align preferences
to prevent collisions with boundary edges.

collisionBoundary.name: collisionBoundary
collisionBoundary.description:
The element used as the collision boundary. By default
this is the viewport, though you can provide additional
element(s) to be included in this check.

collisionPadding.name: collisionPadding
collisionPadding.description:
The distance in pixels from the boundary edges where collision
detection should occur. Accepts a number (same for all sides),
or a partial padding object, for example: { top: 20, left: 20 }.

arrowPadding.name: arrowPadding
arrowPadding.description:
The padding between the arrow and the edges of the content.
If your content has border-radius, this will prevent it from
overflowing the corners.

sticky.name: sticky
sticky.description:
The sticky behavior on the align axis. `partial` will keep the
content in the boundary as long as the trigger is at least partially
in the boundary whilst "always" will keep the content in the boundary
regardless.

hideWhenDetached.name: hideWhenDetached
hideWhenDetached.description: Whether to hide the content when the trigger becomes fully occluded.

positionStrategy.name: positionStrategy
positionStrategy.description: The type of CSS position property to use.

updatePositionStrategy.name: updatePositionStrategy
updatePositionStrategy.description: Strategy to update the position of the floating element on every animation frame.

forceMount.name: forceMount
forceMount.description:
Used to force mounting when more control is needed. Useful when
controlling animation with Vue animation libraries.

ariaLabel.name: ariaLabel
ariaLabel.description:
By default, screenreaders will announce the content inside
the component. If this is not descriptive enough, or you have
content that cannot be announced, use aria-label as a more
descriptive label.

interact with them: once to close the `DismissableLayer`, and again to trigger the element.

Example: threshold of 0.5 would close the drawer if the user swiped for 50% of the height of the drawer or more.

setBackgroundColorOnScale.description: When `false` we don't change body's background color when the drawer is open.

scrollLockTimeout.name: scrollLockTimeout
scrollLockTimeout.description: Duration for which the drawer is not draggable after scrolling content inside of the drawer.

dismissible.name: dismissible
dismissible.description:
When `false` dragging, clicking outside, pressing esc, etc. will not close the drawer.
Use this in combination with the `open` prop, otherwise you won't be able to open/close the drawer.

handleOnly.name: handleOnly
handleOnly.description: When `true` only allows the drawer to be dragged by the `<Drawer.Handle />` component.

snapPoints.name: snapPoints
snapPoints.description:
Array of numbers from 0 to 100 that corresponds to % of the screen a given snap point should take up.
Should go from least visible. Example `[0.2, 0.5, 0.8]`.
You can also use px values, which doesn't take screen height into account.

props.description: When `true`, prevents the user from interacting with listbox

props.description: The content of the menu.

side.name: side
side.description:
The preferred side of the trigger to render against when open.
Will be reversed when collisions occur and avoidCollisions
is enabled.

sideOffset.name: sideOffset
sideOffset.description: The distance in pixels from the trigger.

align.name: align
align.description:
The preferred alignment against the trigger.
May change when collisions occur.

alignOffset.name: alignOffset
alignOffset.description: An offset in pixels from the `start` or `end` alignment options.

avoidCollisions.name: avoidCollisions
avoidCollisions.description:
When `true`, overrides the side and align preferences
to prevent collisions with boundary edges.

collisionBoundary.name: collisionBoundary
collisionBoundary.description:
The element used as the collision boundary. By default
this is the viewport, though you can provide additional
element(s) to be included in this check.

collisionPadding.name: collisionPadding
collisionPadding.description:
The distance in pixels from the boundary edges where collision
detection should occur. Accepts a number (same for all sides),
or a partial padding object, for example: { top: 20, left: 20 }.

arrowPadding.name: arrowPadding
arrowPadding.description:
The padding between the arrow and the edges of the content.
If your content has border-radius, this will prevent it from
overflowing the corners.

sticky.name: sticky
sticky.description:
The sticky behavior on the align axis. `partial` will keep the
content in the boundary as long as the trigger is at least partially
in the boundary whilst "always" will keep the content in the boundary
regardless.

hideWhenDetached.name: hideWhenDetached
hideWhenDetached.description: Whether to hide the content when the trigger becomes fully occluded.

positionStrategy.name: positionStrategy
positionStrategy.description: The type of CSS position property to use.

updatePositionStrategy.name: updatePositionStrategy
updatePositionStrategy.description: Strategy to update the position of the floating element on every animation frame.

disableUpdateOnLayoutShift.name: disableUpdateOnLayoutShift
disableUpdateOnLayoutShift.description: Whether to disable the update position for the content when the layout shifted.

prioritizePosition.name: prioritizePosition
prioritizePosition.description:
Force content to be position within the viewport.

Might overlap the reference element, which may not be desired.

reference.name: reference
reference.description:
The custom element or virtual element that will be set as the reference
to position the floating element.

If provided, it will replace the default anchor element.

disableOutsidePointerEvents.name: disableOutsidePointerEvents
disableOutsidePointerEvents.description:
When `true`, hover/focus/click interactions will be disabled on elements outside
the `DismissableLayer`. Users will need to click twice on outside elements to
interact with them: once to close the `DismissableLayer`, and again to trigger the element.

position.name: position
position.description:
The positioning mode to use,
`inline` is the default and you can control the position using CSS.
`popper` positions content in the same way as our other primitives, for example `Popover` or `DropdownMenu`.

bodyLock.name: bodyLock
bodyLock.description: The document.body will be lock, and scrolling will be disabled.
